  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "On Quora, while you can't block specific topics or questions entirely, you can customize your feed to reduce unwanted content. Here are some steps you can take to reduce the presence of topics related to Trump:\n\n1. **Mute Topics**: Find topics related to Trump that appear frequently in your feed and choose the \"Mute\" option. You can do this by visiting the topic page and clicking on the options menu (usually represented by three dots) to find the mute option.\n\n2. **Unfollow Related Spaces**: Spaces on Quora often center around specific interests or themes. If you're following any spaces that frequently discuss Trump, you can unfollow them to reduce content from those spaces.\n\n3. **Downvote or Dismiss Questions**: When questions about Trump appear in your feed, you can downvote or dismiss them. Doing so will signal to Quora that you prefer not to see similar content in the future.\n\n4. **Adjust Your Interests**: Review and adjust your interests in your profile settings. By unfollowing topics related to Trump, you can help tailor your feed to your preferences.\n\n5. **Provide Feedback**: When you dismiss a question, you sometimes have the option to provide feedback on why you don't want to see it. This can help improve Quora's content suggestions for you.\n\nWhile these steps can help manage the type of content you see, remember it's difficult to block all content about a widely discussed public figure like Trump entirely. However, by actively managing your feed, you can create a more tailored and enjoyable experience on Quora.",
